node.text:
For the past few months, I have been working on creating an online offering that has the same feel and quality content of an in-person event. Together with Soren of @wisdom2events and @guynamedlindsey we have created Committed to the Journey. It is an interview series where I cover topics from relationships, unlocking creativity, healing and growth, my personal story, how inner-work impacts society, and much more. I try to keep my events accessible and this will be no different, for $20 you can access all of the interviews, which is more than 3 hours of content. You can access the videos by going to the top link in my bio or by going directly to vimeo.com/ondemand/committedtothejourney or by checking out my stories. Really excited to bring you this series; in a way this feels like the direct follow up to my first book Inward. I hope it serves you well.

Sending love to all 🙏🏽 #yungpueblo

Hey friends, a segment aired on @nightline on @abcnetwork last night featuring my work as a writer and speaker. It is surreal seeing this summary of things. I didn’t know how everything would turn out when I started sharing my writing on Instagram back in 2015. Grateful to everyone who helped along the way. Special thanks to @lauraecoburn for producing this piece and @danharris and the @tenpercenthappier team for interviewing me. Also @sacredspacemiami for letting us get footage of the event. Sending much love to all beings. #yungpueblo

node.text:
Peace is not passive, it is mental clarity and compassion in action. Your healing not only benefits you and everyone you encounter, but it helps you make better and more humane decisions in a rapidly changing world.

Personal healing is important, but collective healing is also critical. Human beings do not live in a vacuum, our interconnectedness is what gives us the opportunity to thrive. It definitely helps the world when we heal ourselves, but we should also find ways to do our part to support movements for a better and more just world. When people move together around a common cause, history changes.

It is easy to recreate the harm that has happened to us if we never take the time to process it in a healthy way. This is why your healing is a gift to the people who will cross your path in the future.

The same way it is to your personal benefit to not harm others, it is also to your personal benefit for others to be safe from harm and have their material needs met. When more people can truly flourish, the shared happiness of humanity will also increase.

The mental clarity that comes after healing helps us engage more deeply with complexity, which is what we need to understand the issues in front of us so we can substantially decrease direct and indirect forms of harm.

Sending love to all. 🙏🏽🌎 #yungpueblo

node.text:
Letting go is not a one time event, it is a habit that requires consistent repetition to become strong. Sometimes the reaction to the pain is so deep that you will have to observe and release the tension repeatedly to fully cleanse the wound.

Letting go reaches its highest levels when your observation of what is happening inside of you is done with total acceptance. Especially in the mind, adding more tension to the tension that is already there will not make things better. When tension is met with unconditional acceptance, it has the space it needs to naturally unfold and release.

Letting go always seems opaque in the beginning, there is no one way to do it. There are many techniques out there. I personally practice Vipassana meditation and it has helped me tremendously, but I have friends who have had great success in other forms of meditation, journaling, and 1 on 1 therapy.

There is so much out there, what matters is finding something that meets your conditioning where it is at. Something that is challenging but not overwhelming. If you are open to it, please share what has helped you let go in the comments. It is helpful for all of us to see what is working for other people.

Unloading the mental weight of past hurt is never easy, but it is possible, especially when we feel ready for a great transformation.

Sending love to all 🙏🏽🌎 #yungpueblo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by yung pueblo on July 14, 2021. May be an image of text that says '4 things make relationships easier: space to be your own person less control, more trust calm communication selfless listening yung pueblo'.

node.text:
Vibrant relationships often feel like home and freedom.

Trust not only supports harmony but it becomes the foundation for a long lasting partnership. Control, when a lack of trust combines with attachment, can quickly become micromanaging— this leads to the lack of space that makes people feel tense and unable to breathe deeply.

If we cannot understand each other, we will struggle to be good to each other. When communication is calm it is automatically more clear. When we try to voice our perspectives when emotions are high, often this means we are letting an old defense pattern from our emotional history take the lead, walls will immediately shoot up and very little communicating will occur.

Selfless listening is doing our best to view the situation objectively and compassionately so that we can process what's happening with love instead of ego. When we can hear the views of another person without projecting our feelings onto them there is a greater possibility of coming to a deeper understanding, where both people can see each other clearly and make the changes they need to better support each other's happiness.

Sending love to all beings. May we all grow our self awareness. May we all learn that we can simultaneously live in a loving and kind way while also not allowing others to harm us. 🙏🏽🌎 #yungpueblo

node.text:
Self-awareness stops inner turbulence from playing games with your perception.

Sending love to all 🙏🏽🌎 #yungpueblo

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by yung pueblo on July 12, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'it is not about managing your emotions, it is about managing your reaction to your emotions yung pueblo'.

node.text:
Reactions give us the clearest view of what our mind experienced in the past, they are the dense patterns that rise from the deep subconscious as a way to protect us. This form of defense is not based on wisdom, but on survival, when we start expanding our self-awareness, especially during moments of turbulence, we start to see that we have more effective options than just repeating blind behaviors, which produce limited results that generally wipe away our clarity and inner peace in the process.

We are not trying to control or manage the way we feel, we are trying to accept the momentary movements as they weave through the large spectrum of emotions. Moving from one emotion to the next, spending more time in some than others, but still traveling the whole human experience.

When an emotion or perception is strong, we start reacting to it. Strong reactions not only strengthen the emotion we are feeling, but they immediately imprint and accumulate in the subconscious — predisposing us to reacting in a similar way in the future.

We manage our reactions not by controlling them but by bringing awareness into the process — it is hard to change if you cannot see yourself. There is a degree of action that is taken by those who are trying to reclaim their power and no longer repeat the past, the light of awareness becomes a focal point that is turned inward and becomes especially useful when our reaction to a momentary emotion starts to undo our balance and mental clarity. This awareness lights up the darkness and helps us see more options and information during turbulent moments.

When we remember that emotions are impermanent just like everything else in this universe, it becomes easier to stand next to the river that is the human mind and watch as things flow along by. Self-awareness helps in overcoming blind reactions that make already difficult situations more turbulent, without self-awareness it is hard to make choices that differ from the past.

If you are open to sharing, what technique or practice has helped you in letting go, healing, growing and not being controlled by your old reactions?

Sending love to all beings. 🙏🏽🌎 #yungpueblo
